### Description

I have a pipe which injects service that has not been provided by the component where pipe is used.
```typescript
@Injectable()
export class TestService {}

@Pipe({
  name: 'testPipe',
  standalone: true,
})
export class TestPipe implements PipeTransform {
  readonly TestService = inject(TestService);
  transform(item: any) {
    return true;
  }
}

@Component({
  selector: 'app-root',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [TestPipe],
  template: `@if(false && ('' | testPipe)) { }`,
})
export class App {}`
```
In template I use pipe in `@if` statement: `@if(false && ('' | testPipe)) { }` and I get a `NullInjectorError: No provider for _TestService!` but I think I should not because `false` inside `@if` statement should prevent from creating pipe instance.
If I wrap it with another `@if` there is no issue:
```typescript
@if(false) {
  @if('' | testPipe) {

  }
 }
```

